               <p>JOHN FREEMAN. I live in <placeName id="t18280221-302-crimeloc1597">Bishopsgate-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280221-302-crimeloc1597" type="placeName" value="Bishopsgate-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280221-302-crimeloc1597" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280221-302-off1595 t18280221-302-crimeloc1597"></join>. On the 4th of February I lost these handkerchiefs - I was not at home at the time; I know they were in my shop on the 4th- they have my mark on them.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Had you sold any of them? A. Not any.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280221-302-person1682">
                  CHARLES 
                  STANTON
               <interp inst="t18280221-302-person1682" type="surname" value="STANTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-302-person1682" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-302-person1682" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to Mr. Freeman. On the 4th of February I saw the prisoners in the shop for a quarter of an hour, but neither saw them come in nor go out; Forrester brought them into the shop in about five minutes, with the handkerchiefs - some ladies were being served at the time.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280221-302-person1683">
                  DANIEL 
                  FORRESTER
               <interp inst="t18280221-302-person1683" type="surname" value="FORRESTER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-302-person1683" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-302-person1683" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 4th of February, about half-past four o'clock, I saw the two prisoners go into Mr. Freeman's shop; another lad stood outside; I waited till<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182802210143"></xptr>they came out, then followed, and took them at the Marine Society gateway - I took off Smith's hat, and found three of the handkerchiefs; the other three were behind Jones, in the mud - he had dropped them.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. BARRY. Q. Did you see them fall? A. No; they were close behind him; Smith was about a yard off - they could not have fallen from him.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>JONES' Defence. I went to buy a black handkerchief; they wanted 4s., and I did not buy it - I had not seen Smith; nothing was found on me.</p>
               <p>SMITH'S Defence. I was not in the shop.</p>
               <p>JONES - <rs id="t18280221-302-verdict1598" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280221-302-verdict1598" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 14.</p>
               <p>SMITH - <rs id="t18280221-302-verdict1599" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280221-302-verdict1599" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 16.</p>
